<project name="UnderwaterRescue_Search" app="Snap! 11.0.8, https://snap.berkeley.edu" version="2"><notes>Underwater Submarine Rescue - CSC520 Assignment 1

SCENARIO: A submarine must collect 3 beacons (B1,B2,B3) scattered across
20 transit nodes and then dock at any of 3 docking stations (D1,D2,D3).
Some nodes have forced transitions (S7->S8, S14->S15).

STATE: (currentNode, collectedBeacons)
INITIAL STATE: (startState, {})
GOAL: currentNode in {D1,D2,D3} AND collectedBeacons = {B1,B2,B3}
COST: edge weight (energy cost)
HEURISTIC h(n): 3 * uncollected_beacons + 5 * (not at goal state)
  - Admissible: minimum cost to collect a beacon >= 3, to reach dock >= 5
  - Consistent: moving one step changes h by at most the edge cost

HOW TO RUN:
1. Click green flag to initialise
2. Set algorithmChoice watcher to: BFS / DFS / UCS / AStar
3. Set startState watcher to: S0 or S5
4. Broadcast setTC1 / setTC2 / setTC3 to load test cases
5. Click the SearchEngine sprite (or broadcast runSearch)
6. Read results in searchLog and finalPath watchers

TEST CASES:
  TC1: Start=S0, Beacons=B1 B2 B3, Goals=D1 D2 D3
  TC2: Start=S5, Beacons=B1 B2 B3, Goals=D1 D2 D3
  TC3: Start=S0, Beacons=B1 B2,    Goals=D1 D2  (smaller)

OUTPUTS: searchLog (expansion trace), finalPath, finalCost,
         expandedCount, pathLength</notes><thumbnail>data:image/png;base64,</thumbnail><scenes select="1"><scene name="UnderwaterRescue"><notes></notes><hidden></hidden><headers></headers><code></code><blocks></blocks><primitives></primitives><stage name="Stage" width="480" height="360" costume="0" color="255,255,255,1" tempo="60" threadsafe="false" penlog="false" volume="100" pan="0" lines="round" ternary="false" hyperops="true" codify="false" inheritance="true" sublistIDs="false" id="1"><pentrails>data:image/png;base64,</pentrails><costumes><list struct="atomic" id="2"></list></costumes><sounds><list struct="atomic" id="3"></list></sounds><variables>
